-- U.S.-based taxable bond funds post record outflows in latest week -ICI
-- By Sam Forgione
-- Wed Oct 08, 2014 12:22PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Oct 8 (Reuters) - Investors in U.S.-based mutual funds pulled $21 billion out of taxable bond funds in the week ended Oct. 1, marking the biggest outflows from the funds since records began in 2007, data from the Investment Company Institute showed on Wednesday.

Municipal bond funds attracted $788 million, leading to net outflows of $20.2 billion from bond funds over the period, according to data from ICI, a U.S. mutual fund trade organization.  Stock funds posted $1.8 billion in outflows, marking their biggest outflows in four weeks.